         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1 #a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>192</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #a7 #a8 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6 #b7 #b8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:mullerandsieg1916"/></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958a"/><citedRange>152</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4 #a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>154</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>359</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Welche in des Buddha (Śākyamu)ni Lehre Si(ttlichkeit bewahren), Gaben geben, mit Freude (das Wissen) lernen, den Sinn verstehen, ... auf den Wegen den Boden fegen, ...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Who[ever], in the teaching of the Buddha (Śākyamu)ni, keep the moral conduct, give gifts, learn (the knowledge) with joy, understand the meaning, ... sweep the ground on the paths, ...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>359, 413</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5 #a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>413</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>341</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>420f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1968"/><citedRange>224</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Wie ihr es für euch gut befindet, so tuet auch ihr!</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">As you find it acceptable for yourselves, so do you[rselves] also!</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>420-1</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>70</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2 #b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas195